job_description: Data Analyst - job post Prime 8 Consulting 14 reviews Bellevue, WA 98004 • Remote $50 - $65 an hour -  Contract Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $50 - $65 an hour Job Type Contract Data Analyst - Remote Overview In this role we are working on evolving our randomized controlled experimentation capabilities including looking at the multiple platforms, processes, and people involved today into a comprehensive engine with centralized support in one of the largest marketing and sales engines in the world. This role will evangelize and advance the usage, engagement, and satisfaction of Analytics offerings and advocate a product-led mindset across the Analytics team. You will be responsible for delivering cutting-edge analytics products to internal customers, enabling them to make fact-based decisions. You will have the responsibility to shape and lead the development of analytic products across the team. What You’ll Do Own and drive a core set of analytical data products that help teams understand marketing and account trends to make data-driven and informed decisions. Build a brand around analytics data to drive awareness and adoption across various stakeholders by understanding the company and leveraging core marketing principles like product, promotion, and place. Ensure insights are both actionable and measurable and you should be able to build these insights and hypotheses with awareness of practical implementation and implications for the business. Partner with our Digital Analytics and Data Engineering teams to ensure robust and accurate data capture and continuous improvement of data available for both analytics and the wider business. Drive training, process integration, and adoption of reporting solutions to ensure value realization across multiple stakeholders. Engage with and influence business teams to drive alignment. Share knowledge through presentations at regional, channel, and business-wide events, as well as build relationships with analytics teams across the group. What You’ll Have Be able to drive and engage broad projects that will have executive level review. Solid comm skills and soft skills Need to have a backbone to say “no” when needed but in a kind fashion. Need to be comfortable getting technical understanding data landscape and architecture. 5+ years of Product or Program Management experience in a technology organization/dept., including across multiple disciplines. Current or previous experience leading and executing projects in a complex organizational environment and working on several diverse projects at the same time. Current or previous experience in a Business Program Manager type of role within an engineering organization. Bachelor’s degree or higher in an analytical area such as Computer Science, Management Information Systems, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, or a similar field. Product-thinking and leadership experience - solution delivery, product scoping, customer interviewing, needs analysis, etc. Rich product management experience involving responsibility for data platforms or analytics, exhibiting full ownership of the product lifecycle from idea to support cases. Attention to detail and strong at execution. Excellent networking and interpersonal skills with the ability to successfully collaborate across multiple teams and levels. Capable of strong individual contribution and influence across non-direct reporting teams. Strong analytical and communication skills with the ability to influence. Entrepreneurial approach and ability to excel in an ambiguous environment. Prime 8 is a highly respected, woman-owned management consulting firm. We use innovative and outcome-driven approaches to deliver solutions that create lasting results, even after we're gone. The deep expertise of our talented consultants help companies turn ideas into action, implement organizational change, and get products to market quickly using modern practices and technologies. The Prime 8 family of consultants stands out from the crowd. As a group of high-achievers, we hold each other accountable for exceptional work that is built on integrity, honesty, and excellence. We do what we say and finish what we start. Together, we make an impact, have fun and do better for each other and for our customers. Compensation: Prime 8 uses different pay ranges based on level of position, relevant experience, and specific candidate location. The pay range for this role is between $50 and $65 per hour (based on full time employment), plus employee benefits. Employee Benefits: Prime 8 offers a rich package of excellent Medical, Dental (including orthodontic) and Vision insurance (for employees and their families). Prime 8 offers Paid Holidays and Paid Time Off, a 401K Plan, company paid Group Life, STD, LTD, and employee paid Life Insurance and Long-Term Disability options. Prime 8 offers a great referral bonus program for our employees as well. Check out our additional employee benefits! Don’t meet every single requirement? Studies have shown that women and people of color are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single qualification. At Prime 8 Consulting, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive and authentic workplace. If you’re excited about this role but your background/experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the candidate we are looking for, whether for this role or other roles we have in the future.
